# SSH keys allowed to sign commits for pull requests.
#
# This file uses Git's gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile format:
#
#   principal ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAI... optional-comment
#
# The principal is a label Git reports for the matched key. Authorization comes
# from the public key being present in this file, not from a GitHub login or
# repository permission.
#
# The workflow reads this file from the protected base commit, not from the PR
# head, so PRs cannot authorize their own keys. Add keys in a dedicated PR,
# merge it, then use those keys to sign subsequent commits.
#
# OpenSSH key lifetime options can be used to rotate keys without invalidating
# older commits. For example:
#
#   alice valid-after="2026-01-01T00:00:00Z" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3... alice-laptop-2026
